Votic phonetics, morphophonology (grade alternations, gemination), nominal morphology (case, number), pronouns, numerals, comparative degree of adjectives, verbal morphology (person, number, tense, mood, polarity). History of Ingria, language extinction, language shift, language continuum, fieldwork.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the course is to give the basic knowledge of the Votic language (phonetics, grammar, and syntax) in the context of other minor Finnic languages spoken in Ingria. The course pays much attention to the history of the region, the current sociolinguistic situation, language contacts, identities and the problem of a dialect continuum. Also, methodology of field research on a nearly extinct language will be discussed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students will get to know the structure, dialectology, and history of the Votic language, be able to read and analyse Votic texts, understand the typical effects of language contacts in multilingual environment, and get acquainted with the principles of collecting field data from speakers of highly endangered languages.
